\v 20 And when the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w decree|strong="H6599"\w* which he shall \w make|strong="H6213"\w* shall be \w published|strong="H8085"\w* throughout all his \w empire|strong="H4438"\w*, (for it is \w great|strong="H7227"\w*,) all the \w wives|strong="H0802"\w* shall \w give|strong="H5414"\w* to their \w husbands|strong="H1167"\w* \w honour|strong="H3366"\w*, both to \w great|strong="H1419"\w* and \w small|strong="H6996"\w*.  
\v 21 And the \w saying|strong="H1697"\w* \w pleased|strong="H3190"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* and the \w princes|strong="H8269"\w*; and the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w did|strong="H6213"\w* according to the \w word|strong="H1697"\w* of \w Memucan|strong="H4462"\w*:\f + \fr 1.21 \ft pleased…: Heb. was good in the eyes of the king\f*  
\v 22 For he \w sent|strong="H7971"\w* \w letters|strong="H5612"\w* into all the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w provinces|strong="H4082"\w*, into every \w province|strong="H4082"\w* according to the \w writing|strong="H3791"\w* thereof, and to every \w people|strong="H5971"\w* after their \w language|strong="H3956"\w*, that every \w man|strong="H0376"\w* should bear \w rule|strong="H8323"\w* in his own \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, and that \add it\add* should be \w published|strong="H1696"\w* according to the \w language|strong="H3956"\w* of every \w people|strong="H5971"\w*.\f + \fr 1.22 \ft that it…: Heb. that one should publish it according to the language of his people\f*   
\c 2  
\p
\v 1 \w After|strong="H0310"\w* these \w things|strong="H1697"\w*, when the \w wrath|strong="H2534"\w* of \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w Ahasuerus|strong="H0325"\w* was \w appeased|strong="H7918"\w*, he \w remembered|strong="H2142"\w* \w Vashti|strong="H2060"\w*, and what she had \w done|strong="H6213"\w*, and what was \w decreed|strong="H1504"\w* against her.  
\v 2 Then \w said|strong="H0559"\w* the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w servants|strong="H5288"\w* that \w ministered|strong="H8334"\w* unto him, Let there be \w fair|strong="H2896"\w* \w young|strong="H5291"\w* \w virgins|strong="H1330"\w* \w sought|strong="H1245"\w* for the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*:  
\v 3 And let the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w appoint|strong="H6485"\w* \w officers|strong="H6496"\w* in all the \w provinces|strong="H4082"\w* of his \w kingdom|strong="H4438"\w*, that they may gather \w together|strong="H6908"\w* all the \w fair|strong="H2896"\w* \w young|strong="H5291"\w* \w virgins|strong="H1330"\w* unto \w Shushan|strong="H7800"\w* the \w palace|strong="H1002"\w*, to the \w house|strong="H1004"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*, unto the \w custody|strong="H3027"\w* of \w Hege|strong="H1896"\w* the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w chamberlain|strong="H5631"\w*, \w keeper|strong="H8104"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*; and let their things for \w purification|strong="H8562"\w* be \w given|strong="H5414"\w* \add them:\add*\f + \fr 2.3 \ft unto the…: Heb. unto the hand\f*\f + \fr 2.3 \ft Hege: also called, Hegai\f*  
\v 4 And let the \w maiden|strong="H5291"\w* which \w pleaseth|strong="H3190"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* be \w queen|strong="H4427"\w* instead of \w Vashti|strong="H2060"\w*. And the \w thing|strong="H1697"\w* \w pleased|strong="H3190"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*; and he did \w so|strong="H6213"\w*.   
\p
\v 5 ¶ \add Now\add* in \w Shushan|strong="H7800"\w* the \w palace|strong="H1002"\w* there was a \w certain|strong="H0376"\w* \w Jew|strong="H3064"\w*, whose \w name|strong="H8034"\w* \add was\add* \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w*, the \w son|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Jair|strong="H2971"\w*, the \w son|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Shimei|strong="H8096"\w*, the \w son|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Kish|strong="H7027"\w*, a \w Benjamite|strong="H1145"\w*;  
\v 6 Who had been carried \w away|strong="H1540"\w* from \w Jerusalem|strong="H3389"\w* with the \w captivity|strong="H1473"\w* which had been carried \w away|strong="H1540"\w* with \w Jeconiah|strong="H3204"\w* \w king|strong="H4428"\w* of \w Judah|strong="H3063"\w*, whom \w Nebuchadnezzar|strong="H5019"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* of \w Babylon|strong="H0894"\w* had carried \w away|strong="H1540"\w*.\f + \fr 2.6 \ft Jeconiah: also called, Jehoiachin\f*  
\v 7 And he brought \w up|strong="H0539"\w* \w Hadassah|strong="H1919"\w*, that \add is\add*, \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w*, his \w uncle’s|strong="H1730"\w* \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w*: for she had neither \w father|strong="H0001"\w* nor \w mother|strong="H0517"\w*, and the \w maid|strong="H5291"\w* \add was\add* \w fair|strong="H3303"\w* and \w beautiful|strong="H2896"\w*; whom \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w*, when her \w father|strong="H0001"\w* and \w mother|strong="H0517"\w* were \w dead|strong="H4194"\w*, \w took|strong="H3947"\w* for his own \w daughter|strong="H1323"\w*.\f + \fr 2.7 \ft brought…: Heb. nourished\f*\f + \fr 2.7 \ft fair…: Heb. fair of form, and good of countenance\f*   
\p
\v 8 ¶ So it came to pass, when the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w commandment|strong="H1697"\w* and his \w decree|strong="H1881"\w* was \w heard|strong="H8085"\w*, and when \w many|strong="H7227"\w* \w maidens|strong="H5291"\w* were gathered \w together|strong="H6908"\w* unto \w Shushan|strong="H7800"\w* the \w palace|strong="H1002"\w*, to the \w custody|strong="H3027"\w* of \w Hegai|strong="H1896"\w*, that \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* was \w brought|strong="H3947"\w* also unto the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, to the \w custody|strong="H3027"\w* of \w Hegai|strong="H1896"\w*, \w keeper|strong="H8104"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*.  
\v 9 And the \w maiden|strong="H5291"\w* \w pleased|strong="H3190"\w* him, and she \w obtained|strong="H5375"\w* \w kindness|strong="H2617"\w* of \w him|strong="H6440"\w*; and he \w speedily|strong="H0926"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* her her things for \w purification|strong="H8562"\w*, with such things as \w belonged|strong="H4490"\w* to her, and \w seven|strong="H7651"\w* \w maidens|strong="H5291"\w*, \add which were\add* \w meet|strong="H7200"\w* to be \w given|strong="H5414"\w* her, out of the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w*: and he \w preferred|strong="H8138"\w* her and her \w maids|strong="H5291"\w* unto the \w best|strong="H2896"\w* \add place\add* of the \w house|strong="H1004"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*.\f + \fr 2.9 \ft such…: Heb. her portions\f*\f + \fr 2.9 \ft preferred: Heb. changed\f*  
\v 10 \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* had not \w shewed|strong="H5046"\w* her \w people|strong="H5971"\w* nor her \w kindred|strong="H4138"\w*: for \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* had \w charged|strong="H6680"\w* her that she should not \w shew|strong="H5046"\w* \add it\add*.  
\v 11 And \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* \w walked|strong="H1980"\w* every \w day|strong="H3117"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* the \w court|strong="H2691"\w* of the \w women’s|strong="H0802"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, to \w know|strong="H3045"\w* how \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* \w did|strong="H7965"\w*, and what should \w become|strong="H6213"\w* of her.\f + \fr 2.11 \ft to know…: Heb. to know the peace\f*   
\p
\v 12 ¶ Now when every \w maid’s|strong="H5291"\w* \w turn|strong="H8447"\w* was \w come|strong="H5060"\w* to go \w in|strong="H0935"\w* to \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w Ahasuerus|strong="H0325"\w*, \w after|strong="H7093"\w* that she had been \w twelve|strong="H8147"\w* \w months|strong="H2320"\w*, according to the \w manner|strong="H1881"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*, (for so were the \w days|strong="H3117"\w* of their \w purifications|strong="H4795"\w* \w accomplished|strong="H4390"\w*, \add to wit\add*, \w six|strong="H8337"\w* \w months|strong="H2320"\w* with \w oil|strong="H8081"\w* of \w myrrh|strong="H4753"\w*, and \w six|strong="H8337"\w* \w months|strong="H2320"\w* with sweet \w odours|strong="H1314"\w*, and with \add other\add* things for the \w purifying|strong="H8562"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w*;)  
\v 13 Then thus \w came|strong="H0935"\w* \add every\add* \w maiden|strong="H5291"\w* unto the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*; whatsoever she \w desired|strong="H0559"\w* was \w given|strong="H5414"\w* her to \w go|strong="H0935"\w* with her out of the \w house|strong="H1004"\w* of the \w women|strong="H0802"\w* unto the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w*.  
