\p
\v 15 ¶ Then \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* \w bade|strong="H0559"\w* \add them\add* \w return|strong="H7725"\w* \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* \add this answer\add*,  
\v 16 \w Go|strong="H3212"\w*, gather \w together|strong="H3664"\w* all the \w Jews|strong="H3064"\w* that are \w present|strong="H4672"\w* in \w Shushan|strong="H7800"\w*, and \w fast|strong="H6684"\w* ye for me, and neither \w eat|strong="H0398"\w* nor \w drink|strong="H8354"\w* \w three|strong="H7969"\w* \w days|strong="H3117"\w*, \w night|strong="H3915"\w* or \w day|strong="H3117"\w*: I also and my \w maidens|strong="H5291"\w* will \w fast|strong="H6684"\w* likewise; and \w so|strong="H3651"\w* will I \w go|strong="H0935"\w* in unto the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*, which \add is\add* not according to the \w law|strong="H1881"\w*: and if I \w perish|strong="H0006"\w*, I \w perish|strong="H0006"\w*.\f + \fr 4.16 \ft present: Heb. found\f*  
