\v 5 Then the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, Cause \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w* to make \w haste|strong="H4116"\w*, that he may \w do|strong="H6213"\w* as \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* hath \w said|strong="H1697"\w*. So the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* and \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w* \w came|strong="H0935"\w* to the \w banquet|strong="H4960"\w* that \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* had \w prepared|strong="H6213"\w*.   
\p
\v 6 ¶ And the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w* unto \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* at the \w banquet|strong="H4960"\w* of \w wine|strong="H3196"\w*, What \add is\add* thy \w petition|strong="H7596"\w*? and it shall be \w granted|strong="H5414"\w* thee: and what \add is\add* thy \w request|strong="H1246"\w*? even to the \w half|strong="H2677"\w* of the \w kingdom|strong="H4438"\w* it shall be \w performed|strong="H6213"\w*.  
