\v 8 If I have \w found|strong="H4672"\w* \w favour|strong="H2580"\w* in the \w sight|strong="H5869"\w* of the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*, and if it \w please|strong="H2895"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* to \w grant|strong="H5414"\w* my \w petition|strong="H7596"\w*, and to \w perform|strong="H6213"\w* my \w request|strong="H1246"\w*, let the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* and \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w* \w come|strong="H0935"\w* to the \w banquet|strong="H4960"\w* that I shall \w prepare|strong="H6213"\w* for them, and I will \w do|strong="H6213"\w* to \w morrow|strong="H4279"\w* as the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* hath \w said|strong="H1697"\w*.\f + \fr 5.8 \ft perform: Heb. do\f*   
\p
