\p
\v 14 ¶ Then \w said|strong="H0559"\w* \w Zeresh|strong="H2238"\w* his \w wife|strong="H0802"\w* and all his \w friends|strong="H0157"\w* unto him, Let a \w gallows|strong="H6086"\w* be \w made|strong="H6213"\w* of \w fifty|strong="H2572"\w* \w cubits|strong="H0520"\w* \w high|strong="H1364"\w*, and to \w morrow|strong="H1242"\w* \w speak|strong="H0559"\w* thou unto the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* that \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* may be \w hanged|strong="H8518"\w* thereon: then \w go|strong="H0935"\w* thou in \w merrily|strong="H8056"\w* with the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* unto the \w banquet|strong="H4960"\w*. And the \w thing|strong="H1697"\w* \w pleased|strong="H3190"\w* \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w*; and he \w caused|strong="H6213"\w* the \w gallows|strong="H6086"\w* to be \w made|strong="H6213"\w*.\f + \fr 5.14 \ft gallows: Heb. tree\f*   
\c 6  
\p
\v 1 On that \w night|strong="H3915"\w* could \w not|strong="H5074"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w sleep|strong="H8142"\w*, and he \w commanded|strong="H0559"\w* to \w bring|strong="H0935"\w* the \w book|strong="H5612"\w* of \w records|strong="H2146"\w* of the \w chronicles|strong="H1697"\w*; and they were \w read|strong="H7121"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*.\f + \fr 6.1 \ft could…: Heb. the king’s sleep fled away\f*  
\v 2 And it was \w found|strong="H4672"\w* \w written|strong="H3789"\w*, that \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* had \w told|strong="H5046"\w* of \w Bigthana|strong="H0904"\w* and \w Teresh|strong="H8657"\w*, \w two|strong="H8147"\w* of the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w chamberlains|strong="H5631"\w*, the \w keepers|strong="H8104"\w* of the \w door|strong="H5592"\w*, who \w sought|strong="H1245"\w* to \w lay|strong="H7971"\w* \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* on the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w Ahasuerus|strong="H0325"\w*.\f + \fr 6.2 \ft Bigthana: also called, Bigthan\f*\f + \fr 6.2 \ft door: Heb. threshold\f*  
