\p
\v 4 ¶ And the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, Who \add is\add* in the \w court|strong="H2691"\w*? Now \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w* was \w come|strong="H0935"\w* into the \w outward|strong="H2435"\w* \w court|strong="H2691"\w* of the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, to \w speak|strong="H0559"\w* unto the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* to \w hang|strong="H8518"\w* \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* on the \w gallows|strong="H6086"\w* that he had \w prepared|strong="H3559"\w* for him.  
