\v 9 And let this \w apparel|strong="H3830"\w* and \w horse|strong="H5483"\w* be \w delivered|strong="H5414"\w* to the \w hand|strong="H3027"\w* of \w one|strong="H0376"\w* of the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* most \w noble|strong="H6579"\w* \w princes|strong="H8269"\w*, that they may \w array|strong="H3847"\w* the \w man|strong="H0376"\w* \add withal\add* whom the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w delighteth|strong="H2654"\w* to \w honour|strong="H3366"\w*, and \w bring|strong="H7392"\w* him on \w horseback|strong="H5483"\w* through the \w street|strong="H7339"\w* of the \w city|strong="H5892"\w*, and \w proclaim|strong="H7121"\w* \w before|strong="H6440"\w* him, Thus shall it be \w done|strong="H6213"\w* to the \w man|strong="H0376"\w* whom the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w delighteth|strong="H2654"\w* to \w honour|strong="H3366"\w*.\f + \fr 6.9 \ft bring…: Heb. cause him to ride\f*  
\v 10 Then the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w* to \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w*, Make \w haste|strong="H4116"\w*, \add and\add* \w take|strong="H3947"\w* the \w apparel|strong="H3830"\w* and the \w horse|strong="H5483"\w*, as thou hast \w said|strong="H1696"\w*, and \w do|strong="H6213"\w* even so to \w Mordecai|strong="H4782"\w* the \w Jew|strong="H3064"\w*, that \w sitteth|strong="H3427"\w* at the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w gate|strong="H8179"\w*: let \w nothing|strong="H1697"\w* \w fail|strong="H5307"\w* of all that thou hast \w spoken|strong="H1696"\w*.\f + \fr 6.10 \ft let…: Heb. suffer not a whit to fall\f*  
