\c 7  
\p
\v 1 So the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* and \w Haman|strong="H2001"\w* \w came|strong="H0935"\w* to \w banquet|strong="H8354"\w* with \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* the \w queen|strong="H4436"\w*.\f + \fr 7.1 \ft to banquet: Heb. to drink\f*  
\v 2 And the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w said|strong="H0559"\w* again unto \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* on the \w second|strong="H8145"\w* \w day|strong="H3117"\w* at the \w banquet|strong="H4960"\w* of \w wine|strong="H3196"\w*, What \add is\add* thy \w petition|strong="H7596"\w*, \w queen|strong="H4436"\w* \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w*? and it shall be \w granted|strong="H5414"\w* thee: and what \add is\add* thy \w request|strong="H1246"\w*? and it shall be \w performed|strong="H6213"\w*, \add even\add* to the \w half|strong="H2677"\w* of the \w kingdom|strong="H4438"\w*.  
\v 3 Then \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* the \w queen|strong="H4436"\w* \w answered|strong="H6030"\w* and \w said|strong="H0559"\w*, If I have \w found|strong="H4672"\w* \w favour|strong="H2580"\w* in thy \w sight|strong="H5869"\w*, O \w king|strong="H4428"\w*, and if it \w please|strong="H2895"\w* the \w king|strong="H4428"\w*, let my \w life|strong="H5315"\w* be \w given|strong="H5414"\w* me at my \w petition|strong="H7596"\w*, and my \w people|strong="H5971"\w* at my \w request|strong="H1246"\w*:  
\v 4 For we are \w sold|strong="H4376"\w*, I and my \w people|strong="H5971"\w*, to be \w destroyed|strong="H8045"\w*, to be \w slain|strong="H2026"\w*, and to \w perish|strong="H0006"\w*. But \w if|strong="H0432"\w* we had been \w sold|strong="H4376"\w* for \w bondmen|strong="H5650"\w* and \w bondwomen|strong="H8198"\w*, I had held my \w tongue|strong="H2790"\w*, although the \w enemy|strong="H6862"\w* could not \w countervail|strong="H7737"\w* the \w king’s|strong="H4428"\w* \w damage|strong="H5143"\w*.\f + \fr 7.4 \ft to be destroyed…: Heb. that they should destroy, and kill, and cause to perish\f*   
\p
\v 5 ¶ Then the \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w Ahasuerus|strong="H0325"\w* \w answered|strong="H0559"\w* and \w said|strong="H0559"\w* unto \w Esther|strong="H0635"\w* the \w queen|strong="H4436"\w*, Who is he, and where is he, that durst \w presume|strong="H4390"\w* in his \w heart|strong="H3820"\w* to \w do|strong="H6213"\w* so?\f + \fr 7.5 \ft that…: Heb. whose heart hath filled him\f*  
